The rules say those delegates should be Biden supporters, as he is the only candidate still actively seeking the party’s nomination.
In 2016, rowdy Sanders supporters booed some speakers and any mention of nominee Hillary Clinton at the party’s Philadelphia convention.
It’s the other third of delegates — won based on statewide results — that are at issue.
Those rules say Biden should get 346 delegates won by Sanders, Elizabeth Warren, Mike Bloomberg, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar.
Sanders won the Colorado primary on March 3 and took the most delegates from the state.